			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Rob Keast</strong></span> lives with his wife and six-year-old daughter near Detroit, Michigan, where he teaches middle-school and high-school English. He recently finished writing a novel for young adults, for which he is seeking an agent. His longest-running literary creation is Petunia, a rabbit who stars in a new adventure every night at bedtime.</p><a href="/contributors/rob-keast" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
